Definition

Interpreting outcome by follow-up duration

  • Each column represents different cohorts of patients defined by when they started ART.
  • The figure presented as Missing should be excluded from any calculation. This figure may not represent errors in data entry and should not be used for evaluating data quality.
  • The table demonstrates the rate of attrition from the treatment cohort over time - visually represented in the included plot.
  • For example, from the first column (6-months follow-up):
  • The total number of patients is presented as 986
    • 526 patients (Missing subtracted from Total) started ART at least 6 months prior to reporting and their status after 6 months of ART is presented.
